<item>
            <title>[DERBY-6722] GenericStatementContext.cleanupOnError() needs protection from later errors during statement cleanup</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/DERBY-6722</link>
                <project id="10594" key="DERBY">Derby</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;If a statement raises an error and then a subsequent error occurs during statement cleanup, the original error is lost. This is discussed in this email thread:&lt;a href=&quot;http://apache-database.10148.n7.nabble.com/NPE-from-InternalTriggerExecutionContext-cleanup-td141789.html&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://apache-database.10148.n7.nabble.com/NPE-from-InternalTriggerExecutionContext-cleanup-td141789.html&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="12737848">DERBY-6722</key>
            <summary>GenericStatementContext.cleanupOnError() needs protection from later errors during statement cleanup</summary>
